text: Sillanwali (Punjabi,Urdu: سِلانٚوالى‎), is a town of Sargodha District in the Punjab province of Pakistan. The town is tehsil headquarters of Sillanwali Tehsil. It is situated at 31°49'45N 72°32'22E, lying in the southern area of Sargodha, bordering with Jhang District in the Bhatiore area. Population is mainly Muslim and Punjabi speaking.
